.2 snapshots- the README<br>&gt; references files that no longer exist in the snapshots.<br></p><p>It should work, if you are using a release snapshot that doesn’t come with some of the things then you will need to build swift-llbuild first, then the README instructions are still correct.<br></p><p>I’ll update the README to detail this stuff as this is probably the 20th report of this confusion I have read today :(<br></p><p>&gt; Is it possible to divorce the build of swift-pm from the swift<br>&gt; language so that once a stable 2.2 is released I can use it with swift<br>&gt; pm?<br></p><p>I don’t understand.<br></p></div></li></ul></li></ul></div>    </main>
